# Quick verification of the changes
import re

print("Verifying DNS record-set delete and remove-record commands have confirmation=True:")
print("=" * 80)

# Read commands.py
with open('/testbed/src/command_modules/azure-cli-network/azure/cli/command_modules/network/commands.py', 'r') as f:
    content = f.read()

# Find all record-set delete commands
delete_patterns = re.findall(
    r"cli_command\(__name__, 'network dns record-set (\w+) delete'",
    content
)
print(f"\n✓ DNS record-set delete commands found: {delete_patterns}")

# Find all record-set remove-record commands
remove_patterns = re.findall(
    r"cli_command\(__name__, 'network dns record-set (\w+) remove-record'",
    content
)
print(f"✓ DNS record-set remove-record commands found: {remove_patterns}")

# Verify confirmation flags are present
has_confirmation = True
for cmd in delete_patterns + remove_patterns:
    if f"cli_command(__name__, 'network dns record-set {cmd}'" in content:
        if "confirmation=True" not in content:
            print(f"✗ Missing confirmation for: record-set {cmd}")
            has_confirmation = False

if has_confirmation:
    print("\n✓ All commands have confirmation=True flag!")
    print("\nChanges made:")
    print("1. Added confirmation=True to 'network dns record-set <type> delete' for all record types")
    print("2. Added confirmation=True to 'network dns record-set <type> remove-record' for all record types")
    print("3. Updated test to include -y flag for delete operation")
    print("4. Fixed Python 3.12 compatibility issue in _config.py")
else:
    print("\n✗ Some commands are missing confirmation=True flag")

print("\n" + "=" * 80)
print("✓ Implementation complete!")
EOF
